Foot and mouth disease, Mongolia
--------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 24 Nov 2010 from Mr Doloojin Orgil,
director, Ministry of Food and Agriculture, Department of Veterinary
Services, Ulan Bator, Mongolia

Summary
-------
Report type: follow-up report Number 4
Start date: 26 Aug 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 29 Aug 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 24 Nov 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2009
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Khangain ovoljoo, Bayan soum, Tuv
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Nov 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
